MATCH_PATTERN: apps/game-server/src/projections\.ts$|apps/client/src/shells/.*/hooks/usePillStates\.ts$|apps/client/src/shells/.*/(components|hooks).*/[A-Z][A-Za-z]+(Pill|Result|Overlay)[A-Za-z]*\.tsx?$
MATCH_CONTENT: \.(stances|choices|decisions|confessions|answers|guesses|picks|predictions|submitted|submissions|votes|responses)\?\.\[

Cartridge context fields are stripped at projection time, and the set of
stripped fields varies per phase. Client code that checks a type-specific
submission field WILL read `undefined` during the phase where the client
needs it most (COLLECTING). Found during the Pulse B5 "playerActed"
regression (2026-04-16) — the refactor checked `dilemma.decisions` but
that's stripped during COLLECTING, so `needs-action` never cleared even
after the player submitted.

Field stripping map (see `apps/game-server/src/projections.ts`):
  projectDilemmaCartridge:
    COLLECTING → `decisions` stripped, only `submitted` emitted
    REVEAL     → full `decisions` + `results`
  projectPromptCartridge:
    CONFESSION COLLECTING/VOTING → `confessions` stripped
    GUESS_WHO ANSWERING/GUESSING  → `answers` stripped
    (other prompt types emit all fields)

The `submissions` field does NOT exist anywhere in the codebase. Don't
invent fields — grep before relying.

Uniform contract (from 2026-04-16 fix):
  Every prompt + dilemma projection emits
  `participated: Record<string, boolean>` keyed by eligible playerId.
  Always present, phase-independent, type-agnostic. That's the ONLY
  field the client should read for "has this player acted?" checks.
  Dilemma also mirrors it as `submitted` for legacy readers.

Per-type submission fields (use ONLY in REVEAL-phase result content,
not for in-flight participation checks):
  HOT_TAKE             → stances[playerId]  ('AGREE' | 'DISAGREE')
  WOULD_YOU_RATHER     → choices[playerId]  ('A' | 'B')
  CONFESSION           → confessions[playerId] | votes[playerId]
  GUESS_WHO            → answers[playerId] | guesses[playerId]
  PLAYER_PICK          → picks[playerId]
  PREDICTION           → predictions[playerId]
  Dilemma              → decisions[playerId]  (REVEAL only)

Rule of thumb when editing a pill classifier / result card / overlay
router:
  - Participation / needs-action checks → `participated[playerId]`
  - Rendering a specific vote/answer → only after `phase === 'REVEAL'`
    (or an equivalent terminal phase), then read the type-specific field

Source: projections.ts `promptParticipation()` helper +
`projectDilemmaCartridge` inline participated map.
